<task id="waterrocket" xml:lang="en-us">
	<title>How to Make Homemade Water Rocket</title>
	<shortdesc>http://www.wikihow.com/Make-a-Water-Bottle-Rocket</shortdesc>	
	<taskbody>
		<steps>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take a 2 liter bottle and remove label. Take the cap off, but
							save it. You will need it later. 						
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w1.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
				
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take a pen apart (Bic Pens work great) and remove all parts.
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w2.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take the barrel of the pen(the white part) and saw it in half.
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w3.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take the cap of your bottle and outline the size of the pen
							barrel. 
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w4.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take a drill the size of the pen barrel and drill into the
							center of the cap.
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w5.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take a piece of cardboard or similar material and cut out 3-6
							large fins.
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w6.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take a foam football and saw it in half. This will be your
							nosecone.
						</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w7.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Using duct tape, attach nosecone and fins.  Becareful when cutting out fins. </ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w8.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take your pen barrel and attach to a bike pump.  The barrel will act as a connector</ph>
					</b><cite></cite>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w9.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Take pen barrel and insert it into the hole of the cap.  Try to make it fit snugly.</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w10.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Add water into the bottle.  Fill the bottle all the way.  Making sure no leaks.</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w11.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>
			<step>
				<cmd>
					<b>
						<ph>Pump air into bottle. There should be no leaks in the bottle
							for this to work.</ph>
					</b>
					<image align="bottom" href="../images/w12.jpg" width="500"
						height="400" />

				</cmd>
			</step>




		</steps>
	</taskbody>
